25/06/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The OSCE Mission to Croatia said on Tuesday (24 June) that it would hold an international conference on minority integration in South Eastern European (SEE) and Baltic states in Zagreb on 2 July.
The one-day event will gather representatives of the governments of the countries in the region, the OSCE, the European Commission, the Stability Pact for SEE and NGOs.
The conference will compare and analyse the experiences of minority integration and OSCE involvement in the region.
(OSCE Web site, HINA - 24/06/03)
